# Constant error variance assumption broken by observations 36, 11, and 64 look like outliers with around 2x the residual size as the rest of the sample (about 3.5 standardized residuals out). Everything else looks fairly randomly distributed around the mean
# Constant error variance assumption broken by observations 36, 11, and 64 look like outliers with around 2x the residual size as the rest of the sample (about 3.5 standardized residuals out). Everything else looks fairly randomly distributed around the mean
# A suggestion to fix this might be a log transformation of y or a quadratic transformation of x1 or x2.
# standardized residuals are greater than predicted at right tail, suggesting a strong right skew, and therefore, that normality assumption does not hold.
# To fix this I would suggest trying a log-log transformation
